Here is an example implementation of a `show` method for your struct `FloatWithUnits`:
```
struct FloatWithUnits {
    value::Float,
    unit::String
}

# Define a show method for our struct
method FloatWithUnits.show() -> String {
    return "${value} ${unit}".rjust(15))
}
```

This implementation defines a `show` method for your struct `FloatWithUnits`. The method takes no arguments and returns a string representing the value and unit of the struct instance. The implementation uses string interpolation to format the output string.
